Below are **wire (low-fidelity) UI diagrams** and **workflow paths** for the key experiences. These are intentionally simple so you can translate them into Vue components later.

---

## 1) Global App Shell

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Utility Explorer                                   [Transparency] [Status] [Git] |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| [Metric ▼] [Source ▼] [Geo Level ▼] [Period ▼]  [Compare Sources □]  [Copilot ⌄] |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                                  |
|   (Main Content Area: Map / Results)                                              |
|                                                                                  |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Footer:  Data: <Source Name> | Retrieved: <timestamp> | Terms | Contact          |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

---

## 2) Workflow A — Map Explore (default landing)

### Screen: Map Explorer (US view)

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Controls: Metric | Source | Geo Level | Period | Compare Sources | Search         |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| |  MAP (choropleth)            |   |  Details Drawer (collapsed by default)    | |
| |  - States colored            |   |  Click a region to view details           | |
| |  - Hover tooltip             |   |                                           | |
| |                              |   |                                           | |
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| Legend: green(low) -> red(high)   Provenance: RetrievedAt | PublishedAt (if any) |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

### User flow

```
Open app
  -> Choose Metric
  -> Choose Source
  -> Choose Period
  -> Map renders values + legend + retrieved timestamp
  -> Hover region -> tooltip
  -> Click region -> opens drawer (Workflow B)
```

---

## 3) Workflow B — Drilldown + Region Details + History

### Screen: Region clicked (drawer opens)

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Controls …                                                                        |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| | MAP                           |   |  Region Drawer                           | |
| | (State choropleth)            |   |-------------------------------------------| |
| |                                |   |  Kansas (STATE: 20)                      | |
| |                                |   |  Breadcrumb: US > Kansas                 | |
| +------------------------------+   |-------------------------------------------| |
| Legend + provenance              |   |  Current Value Card                      | |
|                                  |   |  14.6 cents/kWh                          | |
|                                  |   |  Period: Dec 2025                        | |
|                                  |   |  Retrieved: Jan 6, 2026 08:15 CST        | |
|                                  |   |  Source: EIA (Terms link)                | |
|                                  |   |-------------------------------------------| |
|                                  |   |  [Drill down to Counties ▸]              | |
|                                  |   |-------------------------------------------| |
|                                  |   |  History Chart (time series)             | |
|                                  |   |  (line chart)                            | |
|                                  |   |-------------------------------------------| |
|                                  |   |  [Export CSV] [Copy link]                | |
|                                  |   +-------------------------------------------+ |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

### Drilldown action paths

```
From drawer:
  [Drill down to Counties]
    -> Map changes to COUNTY boundaries within selected state
    -> If data exists at COUNTY for chosen metric/source:
         county map colors show
       else:
         county map shows boundaries but no fill + “No data at COUNTY level”
```

---

## 4) Workflow C — “No Data at this Geography” (Integrity UX)

### Screen: User drills deeper but source doesn’t support it

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Metric: Electricity Price (STATE only) | Source: EIA | Geo Level: COUNTY          |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| | MAP (COUNTY boundaries)       |   |  Notice                                 | |
| | (no fill colors)              |   |-------------------------------------------| |
| |                                |   |  No data available at COUNTY level       | |
| |                                |   |  for this metric/source.                 | |
| +------------------------------+   |                                           | |
| Legend: disabled                |   |  Options:                                | |
| Provenance shown for last run   |   |  [Switch to STATE view]                   | |
|                                 |   |  [Choose a metric with COUNTY coverage]  | |
|                                 |   +-------------------------------------------+ |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

**Key rule:** boundaries still render; **no fabricated values**.

---

## 5) Workflow D — Compare Sources (same metric, multiple sources)

### Screen: Compare mode enabled

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Metric: Broadband Availability | Compare Sources: [✓] | Period: Latest Common     |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| | MAP                           |   | Compare Panel                            | |
| | Toggle source overlay:        |   |-------------------------------------------| |
| | [Source A] [Source B]         |   | Source A: RetrievedAt, PublishedAt        | |
| |                                |   | Source B: RetrievedAt, PublishedAt        | |
| +------------------------------+   |-------------------------------------------| |
| Legend updates per source       |   | Differences note (definitions/coverage)   | |
|                                 |   | (No blending / no averaging)              | |
|                                 |   +-------------------------------------------+ |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

### Compare flow

```
Enable Compare Sources
  -> UI shows source tabs or split view
  -> user switches source view
  -> chart can overlay multiple series (labeled)
  -> show “values may differ across sources due to methodology”
```

---

## 6) Workflow E — Cross-layer “Scenario” (high electricity + low broadband)

This is a decision-maker friendly view that’s still transparent.

### Screen: Scenario builder (still map-first)

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Scenario: [Electricity Price] HIGH  AND  [Broadband Served %] LOW   Period: Auto |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| +------------------------------+   +-------------------------------------------+ |
| | MAP (STATE choropleth)        |   | Scenario Rules (transparent)              | |
| | Highlight results only         |   |-------------------------------------------| |
| | (e.g., outline states)         |   | Electricity: top 25% threshold = 22.1     | |
| |                                |   | Broadband: bottom 25% threshold = 68%     | |
| +------------------------------+   | Period: Latest common = Dec 2025           | |
| Legend: “Scenario match”        |   | Included: 12 states (all metrics present) | |
|                                 |   | Missing data: 3 states excluded           | |
|                                 |   | [View table] [Ask Copilot]                | |
|                                 |   +-------------------------------------------+ |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

---

## 7) Workflow F — Copilot (read-only) + highlight on map

### Screen: Copilot panel

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Copilot (Read-only)                                                             X |
| Ask: “Show states with high electricity price and low broadband availability”     |
| [Submit]                                                                          |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Result Summary: Latest common period: Dec 2025                                    |
| Table:                                                                            |
|  State | Electricity (c/kWh) | Broadband % | Sources used                          |
|  ...                                                                            ...|
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Citations:                                                                        |
|  - EIA Retrieved: Jan 6, 2026 | Terms link                                         |
|  - FCC Retrieved: Jan 3, 2026 | Terms link                                         |
| Notes:                                                                            |
|  - No values estimated. States missing broadband data excluded.                   |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| [Highlight on map]  [Export CSV]                                                  |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

### Copilot flow

```
User opens Copilot
  -> asks question
  -> system returns table + citations
  -> user clicks “Highlight on map”
  -> map updates to show returned regions highlighted
```

---

## 8) Workflow G — Transparency Page (static ideology + dynamic proof)

### Screen: /transparency

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Transparency & Methodology                                                        |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Principles                                                                        |
|  - Free public data only                                                          |
|  - No ads                                                                          |
|  - No forecasting or gap-filling                                                  |
|  - No silent blending of sources                                                  |
|  - Provenance on every number                                                     |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Coverage & Definitions                                                            |
|  - “City” = Census Place (definition link)                                        |
|  - Geography varies by metric/source                                              |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Sources                                                                           |
|  - EIA: metrics…, terms link…                                                     |
|  - FCC: metrics…, terms link…                                                     |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Live Data Status (dynamic widget)                                                 |
|  Source | Cadence | Last Success | Last Attempt | Status | Notes                  |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Contact / Report an issue                                                        |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

---

## 9) Workflow H — Data Status Page (ops transparency)

### Screen: /status

```
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Data Status                                                                        |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Source Runs                                                                        |
|  - EIA:  Last Success: ...  Next Run: ...  Failures(7d): ...                      |
|  - FCC:  ...                                                                         |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Recent Runs (table)                                                                |
|  Time | Source | Status | Rows Upserted | Error summary                           |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Known Issues / Degradations (optional)                                             |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

---

## 10) Workflow I — CSV Export (region + range)

### Screen: Export action

```
From Region Drawer or Copilot result:
  [Export CSV] -> modal confirmation

+-----------------------------+
| Export CSV                  |
| Metric: ...                 |
| Source: ...                 |
| Region: ...                 |
| Range: 2020-01 to 2025-12   |
| Include provenance: ✓       |
| [Download] [Cancel]         |
+-----------------------------+
```

